{
  "title": [
    "pluck~"
  ],
  "description": "a Karplus-Strong algorithm",
  "origin": "ELSE",
  "categories": [
    "Signal Generators"
  ],
  "inlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "frequency input"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "description": "set frequency and trigger value (normalized to MIDI range)"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float/signal",
          "description": "trigger (determines the maximum amplitude)"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float/signal",
          "description": "decay time in ms"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float/signal",
          "description": "filter cutoff frequency"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float/signal",
          "description": "optional noise input (with the -in flag)"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "outlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "the Karplus-Strong output"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "arguments": [
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "frequency in Hz",
      "default": "0"
    },
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "decay time in ms",
      "default": "0"
    },
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "filter cutoff frequency",
      "default": "around 7020"
    }
  ],
  "flags": [
    {
      "name": "-in",
      "description": "creates an extra right inlet for noise input"
    },
    {
      "name": "-midi",
      "description": "sets to MIDI pitch input"
    }
  ],
  "methods": [
    {
      "type": "midi <float>",
      "description": "non zero sets to MIDI pitch input instead of hz."
    }
  ],
  "body": "[pluck~] is a Karplus-Strong algorithm with a 1st order lowpass filter in the feedback loop. It takes frequency in hertz or midi, a decay time in ms and a cutoff frequency in hz for the filter. It is triggered by signals at zero to non zero transitions or by lists at control rate."
}